            "answer_text": "First of all you need to find out whether the electric connection in your area undergoes voltage fluctuations or not. If the voltage remains stable there is no need to install a stabilizer for your air conditioner (AC), but if frequent voltage fluctuations occur the it is preferable to use a stabilizer. It can be concluded that if you want to remain on the safer side then you should install a stabilizer in addition to your AC, because in case of voltage fluctuations if any damage occurs then first the fuse of the stabilizer will get damage and your AC will remain safe. ",
