            "answer_text": "Yes, as it\u2019s a costly and vulnerable home appliance, you must ensure it\u2019s protection from possible voltage fluctuations. A voltage stabilizer hardly costs 1500/- INR, for ACs upto 1.5 ton, of course, the optimum working voltage range is 190 to 270 V, for such stabilizers, and they cut off if it\u2019s beyond that band, thus offering protection. A stabilizer\u2019s cost increases if the working voltage range you need recedes from 190- 270 V. If the supply at your place has such fluctuations, you must go for a decent voltage stabilizer, no matter the cost. Thanks for A2A Cheers !!! ",
